    /*************************************************************************/
                Directives registry — runtime code & text rewriting.

    A directive is a small named group whose children name a from-target and
    (optionally) a to-replacement. Applying a directive to a field is meant to
    rewrite that field in place:

        target :+ DiRReplaceFoo      replace: swap the matching line
        target :+ DiRDeleteFoo       delete:  drop the matching line
        fileField += DiRSwapInt      text-substrate: rewrite buffer text

    Intended positional shape (Tony 2026-05-28): no from=/to= labels — the
    directive's children ARE the refs. First child = from, second child = to;
    ReplaceDirective walks them via firstInList / nextInParent. A one-child
    directive (DiRDeleteFoo) is a delete.

    Organization: one fixtures+Directives define block, then one runner per
    deliverable, each self-contained and runnable standalone.

