    KNOWN ISSUE — testTextDirective() exits 2 with:
        getFile: could not open file: include: Is a directory
    Root cause (traced, left for Tony to fix in Xcode): getFile does
    pushInput(filing) at Commands.rtn:235 — it not only reads the file into a
    buffer, it QUEUES the file as incant input to be parsed. So loading real
    TAWK source (groups.twk) makes incant parse groups.twk afterward; its first
    line `include /Users/.../groupIncludes` (an unquoted slash-path) can't bind
    as an argument to the incant `include` command, which falls through to
    getFile("include") -> the include/ directory -> error. A self-contained,
    parse-inert fixture (text wrapped in an incant comment) would sidestep it,
    but the underlying getFile/pushInput behavior is Tony's to address.
    ==========================================================================

